  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dde\u0d9b\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0da7\u0ddd\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dba\u0dad\u0dca \u0d87\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Those who gave tokens to buy health oil also came",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A tense situation arose at the Gampaha Co-operative petrol station today (1) when a group of people who had been given tokens had come to collect fuel while handing over 6600 liters of petrol to the health staff.",
        "Since Friday was reserved for providing fuel to the health staff, the health staff had been waiting near the cooperative filling station since around 3 pm yesterday (30) and this questionable situation occurred while preparing to provide fuel this morning.",
        "The vehicles of the health staff were kept at a distance of three kilometers from near the Gampaha Hospital to Oruthota, and due to the questionable situation between the two groups due to the non-delivery of fuel, the police and the army were also called to block the road in front of the filling station.",
        "After the intervention of Assistant Superintendent of Police Mr. Thusitha Kumara, since Friday has been reserved for providing fuel to the health staff, steps were taken to release the fuel today at around 3 pm based on the notification to act accordingly."
      ],
